d is studied using a data set corresponding to an\nintegrated luminosity of 9 fb$^{-1}$ acquired with the LHCb detector in\nproton-proton collisions at centre-of-mass energies of 7, 8 and 13 TeV. The\nstate is consistent with the ground isoscalar $T^+_{cc}$ tetraquark with a\nquark content of $cc\\bar{u}\\bar{d}$ and spin-parity quantum numbers\n$\\mathrm{J}^{\\mathrm{P}}=1^+$. Study of the $DD$ mass spectra disfavours\ninterpretation of the resonance as the isovector state. The decay structure via\nintermediate off-shell $D^{*+}$ mesons is confirmed by the $D^0\\pi^+$ mass\ndistribution. The mass of the resonance and its coupling to the $D^{*}D$ system\nare analysed. Resonance parameters including the pole position, scattering\nlength, effective range and compositeness are measured to reveal important\ninformation about the nature of the $T^+_{cc}$ state. In addition, an\nunexpected dependence of the production rate on track multiplicity is observed.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 2 Sep 2021 16:15:13 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 3 Sep 2021 13:38:25 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 10 Jun 2022 08:35:02 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Thu, 16 Jun 2022 15:52:38 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-06-17"}
