->15N transfer advantages over a\nprolonged CP, multiple contacts that keep both the water and the labile protons\neffectively spin-locked can improve 1H->15N->13C transfers in the presence of\nchemical exchange. The ensuing Looped, Concatenated Cross Polarization (L-CCP)\ncompensates for single J-CP losses by relying on the 13C longer lifetimes,\nleading to a kind of algorithmic cooling that can provide high polarization for\nthe 15N as well as carbonyl and alpha 13Cs. This can facilitate certain\nexperiments, as demonstrated with triple resonance experiments on intrinsically\ndisordered proteins involving labile, chemically exchanging protons.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 2 Sep 2021 16:44:33 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-11-10"}
