ir initial growth. In addition, it raises\nthe peak density of the ambient gas and reduces the SMBH velocity relative to\nit, giving a combined boost to the accretion rate that can reach many orders of\nmagnitude. Our results suggest that a more sophisticated and/or better\ncalibrated treatment of SMBH repositioning is a critical step towards more\npredictive galaxy formation simulations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 3 Sep 2021 13:06:10 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 7 Sep 2021 08:36:02 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 16 Jun 2022 12:31:41 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-06-17"}
