20 with the \\'Echelle spectrograph FLECHAS, and within additional\nTRES-spectra from the Fred L. Whipple Observatory. The main part of this\ncampaign with its 308 reduced spectra, accessible at VizieR, was already\npublished. In this work, which is the continuation and completion of the in\n2015 initiated observing campaign, we found three additional young runaway star\ncandidates.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 3 Sep 2021 13:34:43 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-12-08"}
